Announcing the Drorgs: Ooze Ed. Sofubi Set
A Rotofugi Exclusive!

Via @rotofugi 💚❇️💚

These are not the droids you are looking for....but they are the DRORGS you NEED! 

Join us next Sunday, April 2nd, 1-3pm for a release and signing of DRORGS: Ooze Edition by Nathan Hamill! 

Nathan will be in town exhibiting at C2E2, where he is also giving away an artist edition Fender Guitar, so if you'll be at the convention be sure to stop by his booth to enter the raffle! 

Then, on Sunday we'll be celebrating not only the debut of DRORGS: Ooze Edition, but also the launch of his own signature Coffee Cold with Chicago-based roaster Dark Matter Coffee featuring his LAVABEAR Character — LAVABEAN! 

The figures in the set stand 2.5 and 3 inches tall, respectively, and will be priced at $40 per set — stop by and grab a set and Nathan will sign this Rotofugi Exclusive for you — plus he will have available his Dark Matter Coffee Cold release, as well as a selection of apparel from his Threadless collection.

Rotofugi — 2780 N Lincoln Ave. — Chicago — Open 10am-6pm Daily

Kozik was a hero of mine. Someone, who inspired me at a young age to keep creating art. His poster and silkscreen work’s unparalleled. His art is punk, political, playful, dark…and funny. He then went on to do toys…I got to meet him a handful of times and was always in awe to be in his presence. When I first (really) met him was 2006 or 2007 at Comic Con. I asked him what it was like to move from silkscreens and flyers to vinyl toys. He was very frank and kinda murmured something… “I makes what I likes” was my motto after that. Later on, we’d both work with 3DRetro producing toys and had our stuff at the their booth. I had a few more interactions with him and even got to talk to him a little more in 2012 or 13. He meant so much to me. One of the reasons I do want I do. But the fact that he even knew who I was enough. RIP, sir. You will me missed. Now…back to work, chumps… 💚💚💚#silkscreen #vinyl #vinyltoys #resin #Hiro #frankkozik

Octopup: Cherry Pup 10th Anniversary Ed. 

This weekend marks 10 years of these little creatures!

Releasing tomorrow, Sat. June 24th at 3PM PT for $10 a piece. Vinyls will be bagged and carded.

(Link tree in bio)

NOTE: Will not be translucent like the original. But rather match the color scheme.

“We are excited to be producing our first Japanese vinyl figures with one of our favorite artists, Nathan Hamill. Octopup is the newest character from Nathan and this little guy will be coming out every month in a different color in extremely limited edition. The very first edition (Cherry Pup) is being released on Nathan's birthday 6/25 and is a clear cherry candy flavor-way in honor of that fact that June is National Candy Month (no joke!). 

  The pup is a cute 2inches tall, made in Japan sells for $10 . 3DRetro x Nathan Hamill are only producing extremely small runs of each color so make sure to get yours while they last.” #octopup #octopups #vinyl #sofubi #nathanscreatures

Such terrible news this morning. Paul Reubens is responsible for some of the greatest comedy of the 20th century. Pee-Wee’s Big Adventure is a classic I can quote front to back, side to side and upside down. Sometimes even under water. I saw it when I six with the family in NYC and jumped out of my Dad’s lap when Marge Large reveals her true self. It’s a perfect film. And that’s just one of many wonderful things he created…

He was also a family friend. He was sweet, funny and cool. I couldn’t believe I was getting to listen to stories, converse with and well, just hang out with PW!!! 

RIP, Paul. 

We will miss you dearly. #paulreubens
